### Building URLs
```javascript
function buildPlansUrl(locale, page = 'plans') {
  const baseUrl = 'https://www.adobe.com';
  const localePrefix = locale ? `/${locale}` : '';
  return `${baseUrl}${localePrefix}/creativecloud/${page}.html`;
}

// Example: buildPlansUrl('fr') => 'https://www.adobe.com/fr/creativecloud/plans.html'
// Example: buildPlansUrl('') => 'https://www.adobe.com/creativecloud/plans.html'
```

### Test Configuration
When writing tests or monitors for multiple locales:
- Group by region for parallel execution
- Consider timezone differences for scheduling
- Account for different pricing/currency displays
- Test both left-to-right (LTR) and right-to-left (RTL) languages (Arabic locales)

## Notes
- Total: 92 supported locales
- RTL languages: Arabic variants (eg_ar, kw_ar, qa_ar, sa_ar, ae_ar, mena_ar) and Hebrew (il_he)
- Multi-language countries: Belgium (3), Luxembourg (3), Switzerland (3), Egypt (2), Greece (2), etc.
- Empty string ('') represents US locale (no prefix in URL)

